    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a univariate categorical distribution with six mutually exclusive vehicle type categories. Synthetic percentages were generated using a power-law distribution (\u03bc=25.3%, \u03c3=16.8) to reflect typical market dominance patterns, constrained to sum to 100%. The donut chart variant was selected to optimize data-ink ratio while maintaining proportional accuracy through angular encoding. Cairo's principles are applied through: 1) Immediate hue differentiation between adjacent segments 2) Direct label annotation eliminating legend lookups 3) Conservative use of highlight effects. The 40% inner cutout provides negative space for potential annotations while maintaining area accuracy. Color progression from dark to light greens creates intuitive association with 'green' vehicle technology tiers."
